WEBVTT

00:00:01.851 --> 00:00:05.689 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Big projects require thousands of volunteers

00:00:05.689 --> 00:00:08.558 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
over a period of several years.

00:00:08.558 --> 00:00:12.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
On our program thus far,
we have also considered disaster relief work

00:00:12.729 --> 00:00:15.832 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and branch renovation projects.

00:00:15.832 --> 00:00:17.967 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All of these initiatives require

00:00:17.967 --> 00:00:21.371 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that volunteers fill out an application

00:00:21.371 --> 00:00:24.641 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to be used in these capacities.

00:00:24.641 --> 00:00:27.143 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And there are so many avenues of service

00:00:27.143 --> 00:00:30.213 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that require the submittal of an application.

00:00:30.213 --> 00:00:32.215 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
With that thought in mind,

00:00:32.215 --> 00:00:35.685 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
please carefully watch
the next video entitled

00:00:35.685 --> 00:00:39.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
<i>A New Application</i>
<i>for Processing Applications.</i>

00:00:46.696 --> 00:00:50.166 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Have you ever submitted
an application to expand your ministry?

00:00:53.036 --> 00:00:55.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Since the early 1900’s, 

00:00:55.238 --> 00:00:57.974 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
our organization has used paper applications

00:00:57.974 --> 00:01:00.643 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for many forms of service

00:01:03.513 --> 00:01:07.083 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and faithful workers have responded.

00:01:07.751 --> 00:01:12.522 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This growth is in fulfillment
of Jesus’ words at Matthew 9:37:

00:01:12.522 --> 00:01:15.125 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The harvest is great.”

00:01:17.093 --> 00:01:19.095 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the needs are greater than ever before.

00:01:21.731 --> 00:01:25.068 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Can more workers make themselves available?

00:01:26.269 --> 00:01:29.939 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Can applying for different avenues
of service be simplified?

00:01:31.508 --> 00:01:33.977 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We are pleased to announce

00:01:33.977 --> 00:01:38.047 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
online applications on jw.org®!

00:01:38.915 --> 00:01:43.052 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Publishers will be able to apply <i>online</i>
to expand their ministry!

00:01:46.623 --> 00:01:51.060 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Elders will review
and approve applications online.

00:01:51.995 --> 00:01:54.430 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When needed, circuit overseers will review

00:01:54.430 --> 00:01:56.566 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and approve applications online.

00:01:57.667 --> 00:02:01.604 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your willing spirit
to expand your theocratic service

00:02:01.604 --> 00:02:05.975 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
supports the need
for more workers in many ways.

00:02:11.581 --> 00:02:14.117 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah inspired King David to write:

00:02:14.117 --> 00:02:18.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Your people
will offer themselves willingly.”

00:02:19.656 --> 00:02:23.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And Jehovah’s people
have always wholeheartedly responded.

00:02:26.296 --> 00:02:28.765 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We hope this new online tool

00:02:28.765 --> 00:02:31.501 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
will help you support the Kingdom

00:02:31.501 --> 00:02:34.871 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in whatever way you can,
all to Jehovah’s praise.

00:02:49.319 --> 00:02:51.988 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As you noted,
this provision will be available

00:02:51.988 --> 00:02:55.358 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for those applying
for various privileges of service

00:02:55.358 --> 00:03:00.363 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
beginning January 2020.

00:03:00.363 --> 00:03:04.367 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Technology continues to make advancements.

00:03:04.367 --> 00:03:07.570 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Is there a way to harness such advances

00:03:07.570 --> 00:03:10.440 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for the benefit of Jehovah’s people?

00:03:10.440 --> 00:03:12.475 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Clive Martin,

00:03:12.475 --> 00:03:16.312 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who oversees
the MEPS Department at Warwick,

00:03:16.312 --> 00:03:18.982 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
will discuss a new way

00:03:18.982 --> 00:03:22.819 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to access jw.org® audio files.

00:03:22.819 --> 00:03:24.954 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Please, Brother Martin.

00:03:26.322 --> 00:03:31.327 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We just love the rich supply
of spiritual food on our website and app.

00:03:31.327 --> 00:03:35.632 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
However, some have asked
if there’s an easier way to find

00:03:35.632 --> 00:03:39.769 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and listen
to the audio publications and programs.

00:03:39.769 --> 00:03:42.071 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This would be particularly helpful

00:03:42.071 --> 00:03:45.074 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for many of our dear publishers
who have limited vision

00:03:45.074 --> 00:03:48.111 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and who depend on these audio programs.

00:03:49.312 --> 00:03:52.115 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
With this in mind,
we’re happy to introduce

00:03:52.115 --> 00:03:55.652 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
jw.org® for Amazon Alexa

00:03:55.652 --> 00:03:57.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the Google Voice Assistant.

00:04:01.858 --> 00:04:03.259 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You may have bought

00:04:03.259 --> 00:04:04.794 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
one of these voice assistants

00:04:04.794 --> 00:04:06.396 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to listen to music,

00:04:06.396 --> 00:04:08.398 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
check the news and the weather,

00:04:08.398 --> 00:04:11.134 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or perhaps to control your home appliances.

00:04:11.134 --> 00:04:13.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now you can use it to listen

00:04:13.136 --> 00:04:14.871 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to the content that we need

00:04:14.871 --> 00:04:17.273 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for our regular spiritual routine.

00:04:17.273 --> 00:04:19.642 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s try it out.

00:04:19.642 --> 00:04:24.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Alexa, read the daily text from jw.org.”

00:04:25.348 --> 00:04:27.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Reading the daily text.

00:04:27.350 --> 00:04:29.686 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
